y and imperial politics inform the pastoral narrative and often account for the formalistic change discerned as well as the manner in which Post-Classical diction functions as a targeted, self-conscious linguistic tell-tale of generic evolution. The book is intended for students or scholars working on or interested in Roman pastoral and its generic evolution as well as Neronian Literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aPastoral poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aTheology in literature. 4aCalpurnius Siculus. 4aHirtendichtung. 4aNeronian politics and ideology. 4aRömisches Reich. 4apastoral poetry. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2016z9783110485097oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104726910 cprintz978311046804540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047325440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110473254423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110473254.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016